lead_paragraph: Clinton supporters across the country are just starting to process their feelings about the long roller coaster ride that in their view ended in disaster.

byline.contributor: Katharine Q. Seelye reported from Cambridge, and Claire Cain Miller from Portland, Ore. Reporting was contributed by Jess Bidgood from Belfast, Me.; Alan Blinder from Atlanta; and Anemona Hartocollis and Megan Twohey from New York.
byline.original: By KATHARINE Q. SEELYE and CLAIRE CAIN MILLER

headline.print_headline: … And Those With Dreams That Were Crushed
headline.main: Female Clinton Supporters Are Left Feeling Gutted

snippet: Clinton supporters across the country are just starting to process their feelings about the long roller coaster ride that in their view ended in disaster....
abstract: Interviews with women across nation who supported Hillary Clinton's candidacy for president reveal shock and genuine sense of foreboding; Clinton's failure raises questions about future for female presidential candidates.
